      "id": 1,
      "text": "Pottersville got its name when Serrin Potter bought two mills in 1783, turning the community into a namesake town.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pottersville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1887, over 200,000 baskets of peaches left Pottersville by wagon, reaching Chester and Whitehouse.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        21
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pottersville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The profitable peach industry spurred the Rockaway Valley Railroad to build a spur to Pottersville in 1888.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pottersville%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Most of Pottersville was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1990 as the Pottersville Village Historic District.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
